.Dd March 27, 2025
.Dt PLAKAR-POSTGRESQL 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm plakar-postgresql
.Nd PostgreSQL backup and restoration connector for Plakar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
integration package provides source and destination connectors that back up
and restore PostgreSQL databases using the standard PostgreSQL client tools
.Xr pg_dump 1 ,
.Xr pg_dumpall 1 ,
.Xr pg_restore 1 ,
and
.Xr psql 1 .
.Pp
When configured with a specific database name the source connector uses
.Xr pg_dump 1
to create a single-database dump in custom format
.Pq Li -Fc .
When no database is specified it uses
.Xr pg_dumpall 1
to produce a plain-SQL dump of every database on the server.
.Pp
The destination connector automatically selects the appropriate restore tool:
.Xr pg_restore 1
for custom-format
.Pq Li .dump
records, and
.Xr psql 1
for plain-SQL
.Pq Li .sql
records produced by
.Xr pg_dumpall 1 .
.Sh PREREQUISITES
The following programs must be present in
.Ev PATH
on the machine running Plakar:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "pg_dumpall" -compact
.It pg_dump
Single-database backups.
.It pg_dumpall
Full-server backups.
.It pg_restore
Restoring single-database dumps.
.It psql
Restoring full-server dumps.
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION
Connection details are supplied via a PostgreSQL URI
.Pq the Ar location
parameter
and/or individual fields.
Individual fields override the corresponding URI component.
.Bl -tag -width "username"
.It Ar location
PostgreSQL connection URI of the form
.Li postgresql://[user[:password]@]host[:port][/database] .
.It Ar host
Server hostname.
Defaults to
.Li localhost .
.It Ar port
Server port.
Defaults to
.Li 5432 .
.It Ar username
Authentication username.
.It Ar password
Authentication password.
Passed to the PostgreSQL tools via the
.Ev PGPASSWORD
environment variable.
.It Ar database
Database name.
For the
.Em source
connector: if set, only this database is backed up
.Pq pg_dump ;
if omitted, all databases are backed up
.Pq pg_dumpall .
For the
.Em destination
connector: target database for
.Xr pg_restore 1 ;
if omitted the name is inferred from the dump filename.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Configure a source that backs up a single database and run a backup:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ plakar source add mypg postgresql://postgres:secret@db.example.com/myapp
$ plakar backup @mypg
.Ed
.Pp
Configure a source that backs up all databases:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ plakar source add mypg postgresql://postgres:secret@db.example.com/
$ plakar backup @mypg
.Ed
.Pp
Configure a destination and restore a snapshot:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ plakar destination add mypgdst postgresql://postgres:secret@db.example.com/myapp
$ plakar restore -to @mypgdst <snapid>
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr pg_dump 1 ,
.Xr pg_dumpall 1 ,
.Xr pg_restore 1 ,
.Xr psql 1
